# Cyrius Field Notes — v5.10.x cycle retrospective
# Written 2026-05-10 mid-cycle at v5.10.39 ship (typed-simd ABI
# arc close). v5.10.x is still in flight (closeout pinned at
# v5.10.46); this entry captures slots .0 through .39 — the
# REAL TYPE SYSTEM arc + the typed-simd ABI arc + the v5.10.x
# infrastructure bugs that surfaced en route.
#
# Companion to v59x.cyml (v5.9.x cycle), v58x_back_half.cyml,
# and foldin_arc_v57_v59.cyml. Two big arcs landed parallel:
# REAL TYPE SYSTEM (Phase 1-5 across v5.10.1-.26) and the
# typed-simd value-type ABI (11 phases across v5.10.28-.39).
# Plus 5 TLS surface slots (sandhi 1.3.x unblocks), agnosys
# 1.1.12 closeout cascade, SIMD primitive expansion + cross-
# arch fix, and the v5.10.0 P(-1) hardening foundation.
#
# 39 patches over 5 days (2026-05-06 → 2026-05-10) — closes
# in on v5.9.x's record (44 patches over 2 days) but at lower
# patches-per-day, reflecting two heavier multi-slot ARCS vs
# v5.9.x's many small ones.
#
# 1 entry.

[[entries]]
name = "v510x_cycle_retro_through_39"
description = "v5.10.x retrospective slots .0-.39: REAL TYPE SYSTEM 5-phase arc, typed-simd 11-phase value-type ABI arc, TLS 0-RTT surface, REAL TYPE SYSTEM Phase-3 generalize, install.sh symlink-collision discovery. Two heavy arcs in parallel; one cycle-wide locname-staleness bug class with three distinct surfacings. Plus the pattern of pre-planned splits replacing lazy deferment."
category = "cyrius"
tags = ["retrospective", "agent", "v5.10.x", "real-type-system", "typed-simd", "f64v2", "f64v4", "tls", "0rtt", "sandhi", "agnosys", "install"]
content = """
v5.10.x is the cycle of TWO BIG ARCS landing in parallel:

1. **REAL TYPE SYSTEM** (v5.10.1-.26, 5 phases) — agnosys-driven
   type-annotation work. Surface audit + bulk annotation
   (Phase 1A, v5.10.22), type vocabulary close (1B, .23),
   call-site type check (Phase 2, .24), Phase 3 generalize
   (registry-based overload dispatch, .25), default-on flip
   + silent-regression repair (Phase 5, .26).

2. **Typed-simd value-type ABI** (v5.10.28-.39, 11 phases) —
   `f64v2` + `f64v4` as first-class 16/32-byte primitive value
   types with end-to-end consumer ABI. Five backends fully
   support pair-register return (XMM0 / V0 NEON / r0+r1 cx /
   inheritance for macho-arm) plus retptr-style on Win64 PE.
   Value-form param ABI (callee + caller split-counter) at
   v5.10.38; overload dispatch + typed wrappers at v5.10.39
   close the arc. **hisab benchmark gap-close work depends on
   this arc** — the keystone consumer.

Plus parallel work:

- **TLS surface completion** (v5.10.13, .21, .27, .34) —
  4 slots of TLS hook work driven by sandhi 1.3.x filings.
  Started at .13 with typed wrappers around libssl symbols
  (`tls_set_alpn` / `_verify`); .21 closed the session-cache
  + 0-RTT primitives; .27 added staged-connect for the timing
  window; .34 closed the client-side acceptance-status surface
  (sandhi 1.3.2 0-RTT unblock).

- **agnosys 1.1.12 cascade** (v5.10.7, .8, .10, .12, .14) —
  multi-slot follow-on from v5.9.x. Str-typed struct field
  inference, `#derive(Serialize)` JSON-escape fix, shadow-lib
  diagnosis, defensive `lib/fnptr.cyr` rewrite, multi-stack
  `#derive` directives.

- **SIMD primitive expansion** (v5.10.16, .17) — cross-arch
  close for f64v_add/sub/mul/div/sqrt/abs/fmadd PLUS three
  new keystone primitives (dot, scale, axpy) for hisab.
  v5.10.16 also paid 3.5 years of latent aarch64-stub +
  x86-codegen debt that programs/simd_expand_test.cyr had
  hidden because it was never wired into check.sh.

- **v5.10.0 P(-1) hardening foundation** + v5.10.20 P(-1)
  sweep — the cycle's process discipline anchors.

KEY PATTERNS THAT RECURRED

**Pre-planned split as a replacement for lazy deferment.** The
v5.9.x feedback ("lazy splits where I could've done the harder
piece but chose not to") shifted the cycle's slot scoping
toward bigger but coherent units. The typed-simd ABI arc was
the test case: 11 phases pre-planned at v5.10.33 ship; user
explicitly asked "A+B in .38; C as .39" at the .38 entry
(genuine multi-piece, not lazy split). The result: arc closed
in 12 slots flat with no mid-flight reshuffles.

**Premise-check at slot entry.** The v5.7.x discipline carried
forward — when the .33 typed-wrapper work surfaced an
apparently-disp-shift bug, the v5.10.35 slot was pinned with
"diagnose first, fix second." Diagnosis showed the actual bug
was locname-staleness (NOT emit-side disp shift); the .33
ship-note's hypothesis was wrong. Slot still shipped because
the diagnostic work itself was the deliverable.

**Cross-arch propagation is mandatory.** Every compiler-side
ABI change was verified on pi (aarch64 Linux real HW), ecb
(macOS Mach-O arm64 via codesign), cass (Win64 PE) in the
SAME slot — not deferred. v5.10.31 ABI Phase 4 PE retptr-
style work ran end-to-end at slot entry. v5.10.37 f64v4 hit
an aarch64 LDUR Q imm9 range overflow at slot-entry test;
fix landed in-slot via X9 deep-frame fallback.

**Sovereignty discipline tightened.** v5.10.36 user direction
re-set the rule: cyrius by default, non-cyrius (bash/python/C)
ONLY in extreme bootstrap cases ("the egg"). Pre-v5.10.x the
project had bash regression scripts; closeout investigation
at v5.10.46 will retire most via cyrius gates in
programs/check.cyr.

THREE LOCNAME-STALENESS SURFACINGS

The v5.10.x cycle surfaced the SAME bug class THREE times,
each in a different parse path:

1. **v5.10.35 — PARSE_SIMD_EXT 3-arg intrinsics**
   (f64v_abs/sqrt/dot/scale/axpy). Stash slots from EFLSTORE
   didn't clear locname; stale "r" from a prior fn's parse
   at the same slot caused FINDLOCAL("r") in `return r;` to
   pick up the stash slot (containing &r pointer-VALUE)
   instead of the real var. Fixed with `_SIMD_STASH` helper
   that clears locname[idx] = -1.

2. **v5.10.38 ship verification — ptyp 89-91 missed**.
   v5.10.35 fixed PARSE_SIMD_EXT but f64v_add/sub/mul live
   at a DIFFERENT dispatch (ptyp 89-91 in parse_expr.cyr,
   not in PARSE_SIMD_EXT). v5.10.35 missed them. The bug
   stayed latent because pre-v5.10.39 lib/simd.cyr's
   pointer-form wrappers had a stable locname layout. The
   v5.10.39 lib/simd.cyr rewrite (adding value-form
   siblings, doubling fn count, churning locname slots)
   made the stale-collision reliable.

3. **v5.10.39 fix-in-slot** — same `_SIMD_STASH` pattern
   applied to ptyp 89-91. Bisection diagnosis: reverting
   lib/simd.cyr fully made the test pass with v5.10.39
   dispatch intact, isolating to lib/simd.cyr changes; direct
   `f64v2_add_ptr(&x, &y)` ALSO failed, isolating to the body
   (not the overload dispatch). Same staleness pattern.

LESSON: When fixing a bug class, AUDIT FOR DUPLICATES across
the codebase. parse_expr.cyr has multiple intrinsic dispatch
sites; the v5.10.35 fix should have grepped for ALL bare
EFLSTORE calls in PARSE_SIMD-adjacent dispatchers, not just
the one that triggered. Pin: when fixing locname / dispatch /
table-related bugs, treat the fix as cross-path applicable
until proven otherwise.

INSTALL.SH SYMLINK COLLISION (v5.10.37 ship discovery)

`install.sh:224-235` uses `cp -L lib/*.cyr` to copy stdlib
into the snapshot dir. When `lib/<dep>.cyr` (e.g. mabda) is a
symlink set up by `cyrius deps` resolution into
`~/.cyrius/deps/<dep>/<ver>/dist/`, AND the snapshot dir
already has a parallel symlink to the same real file, cp -L
dereferences both and exits with "same file" error. `set -e`
makes this fatal. Execution exits BEFORE the symlink-update
block at install.sh:249-251 — so `~/.cyrius/bin` /
`~/.cyrius/current` stay pointing at the previous version.

Symptom: cyrius prompt-info reads through the stale
`~/.cyrius/bin/cc5` symlink, renders wrong version on the
user's prompt, looks like "starship.toml corruption" from
the user's perspective.

User-side discovery 2026-05-10 (v5.10.37 work). Root cause
confirmed via manual repro. Fix is pinned in v5.10.46
closeout: change `cyrius deps` to physical-copy lib/<dep>.cyr
(not symlink) — option C from the user discussion. Pre-fix
manual workaround: `rm -rf ~/.cyrius/{bin,lib} && ln -sf
versions/$(cat VERSION)/{bin,lib} ~/.cyrius/ && echo VERSION
> ~/.cyrius/current` after every version-bump.

LESSON: Bootstrap-adjacent install scripts that silently fail
(via `set -e` exit) instead of loudly verifying their
end-state leave the system in inconsistent state. closeout
investigation pin: add a `readlink ~/.cyrius/bin` verification
step at the tail of install.sh's --refresh-only path that
HARD-FAILS if the symlink wasn't updated to the new version.
Silent failure mode survived multiple version bumps because
`cyrius --version` (which reads VERSION file directly) showed
correct info while `cyrius-prompt-info tool` (which reads
through ~/.cyrius/bin/cc5) showed stale. Two version-discovery
paths diverged.

DOC-HEALTH SCAFFOLD (v5.10.34)

Adopted the agnosticos doc-health.md ledger pattern. Cyrius's
tree is ~61 markdown files (vs agnosticos's ~265) so the tier
structure is leaner. Ledger lives at `docs/doc-health.md` —
"living ledger of per-doc currency" — refreshed when docs are
touched (NOT a one-time audit). Per-tier fresh / stale /
read-through / archived classification. Bumped at v5.10.35
(threat-model + fncall-abi refreshes).

This pattern should propagate to other ecosystem repos as they
accumulate doc surface — see agnosticos's
first-party-documentation.md for the convention codification.

TWO-BIT PER-FN STORAGE PATTERN (v5.10.38 simd_mask)

When adding per-fn metadata, claim from the reserved 32 KB
heap-map gap (the 0x1282000 region) and encode 2 bits per
param into a single 64-bit slot. simd_mask uses this pattern
to record which params are f64v2 (01) / f64v4 (10) / int-class
(00). 32 params per fn (cap matches existing param caps).
PARSE_FNCALL reads the mask to route value-form args into
XMM/V regs (cyrius-internal split-counter, NOT SysV-strict).

Don't use new per-fn 32 KB blocks for orthogonal data — squeeze
into existing slots when the data fits.

WHAT CARRIES FORWARD INTO v5.10.40-.46

Pinned remaining slots (per docs/development/roadmap.md):
- **v5.10.40** — Lex dedup hot-path optimization
- **v5.10.41** — Fixup phase optimization
- **v5.10.42** — `lib/tls.cyr` hook-surface contract audit
- **v5.10.43** — macOS arm64 struct-by-value calling-convention
- **v5.10.44** — Defensive sweep (5-item bundle)
- **v5.10.45** — Win64 PE `println` silent + exit-code fix
- **v5.10.46** — v5.10.x cycle closeout (CLAUDE.md 11-step pass)

Plus held items: Class B FFI / wgpu fncall6 ABI (mabda B1/B2 —
held pending mabda 3.0.0 GA), `cyrius deps` file-copy fix
(closeout-investigation pin).

EMERGENT FEEDBACK NORMS

- **Don't propose scope shrink mid-flight** (v5.10.x reinforced
  v5.9.2 pin). v5.10.38 split A+B/.38 + C/.39 was PRE-PLANNED
  at slot entry per user explicit direction; not mid-flight.
- **Bumping versions / writing CHANGELOG entries needs explicit
  go-ahead** (v5.9.20 pin still active). Continued to apply
  through v5.10.x; multi-slot chains shipped with user `5.10.X
  is out; ...` cue at each boundary.
- **Cross-arch verify is in-slot, not closeout deferred**
  (memory pin `cross_arch_propagation_mandatory`). v5.10.x
  cycle exercised pi + ecb + cass at every compiler-side slot.
- **Don't add unrequested defaults to user config**
  (v5.10.36 starship.toml restoration — DON'T pad with
  "sensible defaults" that override the tool's built-in
  defaults). Applies broadly to any user dotfile restore.
- **Sovereignty — non-cyrius only when cyrius literally
  cannot do the work** (v5.10.36 hardened). The egg
  (bootstrap.sh, install.sh, dlopen-helper.c) is the only
  exception. New regression-style work goes in
  programs/check.cyr, not bash.

CYCLE STATS AT v5.10.39

- 39 patches in 5 days (2026-05-06 → 2026-05-10)
- 19 in-cycle bug surfacings (latent debt found + fixed)
- 12 of those were locname/heap/symlink invariant violations
- 11 typed-simd ABI phases shipped
- 5 REAL TYPE SYSTEM phases shipped
- 4 TLS surface slots
- check.sh gate count: stable at 66
- cyrius test count: 132 → 141 (+9 gates)
- cc5 size: x86 753,768 → 797,464 (+43,696 B, +5.8%)
- cc5_aarch64 size: 463,776 → 485,696 (+21,920 B, +4.7%)
- api-surface snapshot: 2,769 → 2,873 (+104 public fns)

The size growth tracks honest feature work; no bloat from
silent regressions. The cycle's discipline: every slot shipped
EITHER a feature OR a fix, never a "refactor that introduces
new state without consumer payoff."
"""
